    <thetext>Description of problem:
Under X - it was possible to use the keyboard to navigate between the different icons in the status icons panel. Under Wayland - any keystroke is sent to the active window.


How reproducible:
Every time

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Open the status icons panel by hovering over the lower-left corner of the screen. Alternatively - Navigate to the &quot;Status Icons&quot; icon using the Ctrl+Alt+Shift shortcut.
2. Once open - try navigating between the icons on the Status Icons panel using the keyword. 


Actual results:
Any keystroke (left/right/enter) will be applied to the active window instead of the icons in the status icons bar.

Expected results:
Navigation will be done on the status icons bar. Enter key will open the highlighted icon.</thetext>
